ActOther Than Statutory Authority
SubjectConfirmation of Canoe Creek Indian Reserve No. 1
PrecisOrder confirming that 1.00 hectare (2.47 acres) of land was set apart on April 14, 1926 for the use and benefit of the Canoe Creek Indian Band now known as the Stswecem’c Xgat’tem First Nation as CANOE CREEK INDIAN RESERVE NO. 1, located in the Thompson-Nicola Regional District at approximately 63 kilometres from the Town of 100 Mile House, British Columbia.
